# App Content Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Assessment Answers] --> B[Detect Difficulty / Flag]

    B --> C1[Emotional Reactivity]
    B --> C2[Task Avoidance / Incompletion]
    B --> C3[Inconsistency / Burnout]
    B --> C4[Academic / Cognitive Strain]
    B --> C5[Shame / Self-Criticism / Avoidance]
    B --> C6[Life Management Stress]

    C1 --> D1[Topics: Emotional regulation, nervous system understanding]
    C1 --> E1[Outcome: Reduce self-blame and confusion]

    C2 --> D2[Topics: Executive function, task initiation, system design]
    C2 --> E2[Outcome: Replace moral blame with practical systems]

    C3 --> D3[Topics: Energy management, sleep, hyperfocus]
    C3 --> E3[Outcome: Stabilize output without overexertion]

    C4 --> D4[Topics: Academic skills, organization, anxiety context]
    C4 --> E4[Outcome: Improve academic self-efficacy]

    C5 --> D5[Topics: Shame cycles, self-trust, grief]
    C5 --> E5[Outcome: Reduce avoidance loops]

    C6 --> D6[Topics: Daily life skills, admin, money, decision-making]
    C6 --> E6[Outcome: Reduce overall stress load]

  
### How it works

- **Assessment answers ** generate **flags** (difficulty areas).  
- Each **flag maps** to a **cluster of topics**.  
- The app shows **primary lessons** for that flag.  
- Every set of lessons has a **specific outcome goal**.  


